I’m getting out of AKs so I have for sale an Arsenal Legion SGL-21.  This went to AK USA and had the barrel cut and the brake pinned and welded for an overall length of 16.5".  The original polymer furniture has been replaced with an Ace skeleton stock, Midwest Industries quad rail, Magpul pistol grip and AFG.  Round count is around 1100-1200.  I’ll also include a side mount scope rail.
Info from the manufacturer:
From the combined effort of Legion Ltd, the custom shop of the legendary Izhmash Factory in Russia, and Arsenal, Inc. of Las Vegas, Nevada comes the SGL21 (Saiga) rifle in 7.62x39 caliber.
Manufactured by Legion Ltd in Russia and converted by Arsenal, Inc. in the United States, the SGL21 rifle has everything that collectors and shooters have been looking for – hand selected premium components, custom-shop attention to detail by Legion Ltd, and Arsenal, Inc.’s highest standards of workmanship, give this rifle its superior quality.
Arsenal, Inc. converts the SGL21 rifles in the United States with 922r compliant parts and fills them with features not seen on any other factory Saiga rifles. Performing the most difficult modifications to achieve, Arsenal, Inc. has done a substantial work for the customer. The end result is the highest quality SGL21 rifle with the most desired features which have not been available before. Every unit is laser sighted and test fired.
To make this rifle the perfect Russian AK available in the market, Arsenal, Inc. has taken all the necessary steps to ensure all the components and features are true to its original configuration. The receiver of SGL21 rifle has the proper markings on both sides without any extra commercial markings including the legendary Izhmash Factory logo, the upward pointing arrow in triangle. The markings on both sides of the receiver are done with the correct font type and size and placed in their proper locations. The receiver of SGL21 features proper magazine dimples on both sides and original “X” and “Y” shaped reinforcement stampings.
On the right side, it has correctly positioned notches for the safety lever, marked with letters “S” and “F” and no additional openings at the bottom forward portion of the receiver. The components and features on the new SGL21 rifle resemble true Russian AK rifle, including the safety lever with correct shape and properly positioned dimple, the correct trigger guard with magazine catch and the correct bullet guide enabling SGL21 to accept any standard AK magazine, the 1000 meter rear sight leaf, the highest quality Arsenal, Inc. double stage fire control group (hammer, trigger and disconnector), original Arsenal, Inc. mil-spec polymer furniture, including the handguards, pistol grip, and the original Warsaw pact length buttstock, the retainer for lower handguard, the correct gas tube, original gas block with the correct vent holes, a guide hole for the cleaning rod and accessory lug, correct AK-74 type front sight block with 24x1.5mm right-hand threads and bayonet lug.

title: For Sale:  M16A1 5.56mm/.223 Replica
postcontent: Took about two years to find all the period correct parts, and unfortunately finances force me to consider selling.Build parts:Colt M16A1 parts kit, including gas block, tube, M16 BCG, charging handle, A1 buttstock w/ storage compartment, etc.Nodakspud NDS-16 Retro LowerSemi-auto Lower parts kit with ALG QMS triggerGreen Mountain Pencil Barrel, 1:8 twist(The rifle twist and QMS trigger are the only period-incorrect parts, chosen to make the rifle more pleasant to shoot and able to stabilize wider varieties of ammo.)Please keep in mind this retro M16A1 replica was built with a specific goal- to replicate my Dad's rifle based on old pictures and to be a shooter.  Given that he was there later in the war, ~1969-1972, my goal was to build the M16A1 as it was during that time.  This isn't meant to be a very early example or any sort of prototype M16.  It's meant to be a common issue that would've been in the hands of a 101st Airborne LT and his platoon during the late '60s or so.  By this time 30rd magazines were standard, A1 birdcage flashhider, etc.  The only two things that I didn't keep period correct:  I used a barrel with 1:8 twist so it can shoot more diverse modern ammo and I used a ALG QMS trigger instead of  the notoriously bad Colt milspec.  I wanted the rfle to be a pleasant shooter while keeping the feel and outward look of the M16A1 service rifle.

An ambidextrous safety makes the P938 easy for left- and right-handed shooters. The Blackwood features a natural stainless steel slide and black hard coat anodized alloy frame, paired with Hogue Blackwood grips.
